    {
      "id": "PopularPost111473",
      "post_content": "**Aaron's Random Card Comment of the Day #20, 10/22/10**   \n   \nAnother day, another red enchantment meant to hose counterspells without explicitly saying so. Price of Glory was released one year after the last card I talked about that did this, Monday\u2019s [Tectonic Instability](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tectonic Instability). I guess R&D was having serious trouble with counterspell decks at that time and found the best way to hose them was with nasty hate like this.\n  \n   \nDespite being almost strictly worse than the paragon of control-hosers, [City of Solitude](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=City of Solitude), this one at least did its job. R&D knew it was going to have an impact, as it was previewed on the now-defunct Sideboard.com by one Brian Kibler nine years ago. I\u2019ve seen it in various sideboards in Standard decks from that era, and there was a time where this was showing up in Vintage sideboards as well. Not only is it good against counters, but anything that might require mana on an opponents\u2019 turn, like activating a [Circle of Pro](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Circle of Pro)... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Aaron_Forsythe",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost111473\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_post\"><b>Aaron's Random Card Comment of the Day #20, 10/22/10</b> <br/> <br/>Another day, another red enchantment meant to hose counterspells without explicitly saying so. Price of Glory was released one year after the last card I talked about that did this, Monday\u2019s <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Tectonic Instability\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tectonic Instability\">Tectonic Instability</a>. I guess R&amp;D was having serious trouble with counterspell decks at that time and found the best way to hose them was with nasty hate like this.\r<br/> <br/>Despite being almost strictly worse than the paragon of control-hosers, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"City of Solitude\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=City of Solitude\">City of Solitude</a>, this one at least did its job. R&amp;D knew it was going to have an impact, as it was previewed on the now-defunct Sideboard.com by one Brian Kibler nine years ago. I\u2019ve seen it in various sideboards in Standard decks from that era, and there was a time where this was showing up in Vintage sideboards as well. Not only is it good against counters, but anything that might require mana on an opponents\u2019 turn, like activating a <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Circle of Pro\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Circle of Pro\">Circle of Pro</a>... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 111473)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '111473'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy5180\">Aaron_Forsythe</span>\r\n                                (10/22/2010 3:24:36 PM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n</div>"
